title: The Life of Charlotte Bronte Volume 2
creator: Elizabeth Cleghorn Gaskell
description: LibriVox recording of The Life of Charlotte Bronte Volume 2, by Elizabeth Cleghorn Gaskell Volume 1 is already available. Charlotte Bronte was a British author, the eldest of the three famous Bronte sisters who have become standards of English literature. She is best known for her novel Jane Eyre, one of the greatest classics of all times. Just two years after Charlotte's death, her friend Elizabeth Gaskell wrote her biography. Want to know more about Charlotte Bronte? If you do, please read this biography. Summary by Stav Nisser. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
